-- Julius Baer says found no evidence of market abuse in forex probe
-- By Oliver Hirt. 
-- Mon Mar 31, 2014 02:21AM EDT
-- None



ZURICH, March 31 (Reuters) - Swiss bank Julius Baer <BAER.VX> said on Monday an internal investigation had found no evidence of foreign exchange market abuse behaviour.

Switzerland's competition watchdog said on Monday it had opened an investigation into several Swiss, British and U.S. banks over possible collusion to manipulate foreign exchange rates. [ID:nL5N0MS0W5] "The internal investigation has shown no indication whatsoever of market abuse behaviour," a spokesman said, adding that the bank would co-operate with the investigation.